comments: Quickley (NYK) and Garland (CLE) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Hartenstein (NYK) grasps Allen's (CLE) jersey and releases it as marginal contact occurs during the pursuit of the long rebound.

Randle (NYK) extends his arm and delivers incidental contact to Mobley's (CLE) face.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Quickley (NYK) establishes himself in Okoro's (CLE) path and is firming up when contact occurs.

Hartenstein (NYK) is moving forward in a natural forward direction when he makes incidental contact to Garland's (CLE) face who is attempting to clear his path.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Mobley (CLE) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Mitchell (CLE) initiates contact to Brunson's (NYK) front that affects his SQBR during the drive.
Allen (CLE) is moving alongside Randle's (NYK) path and marginal body contact occurs during Randle's (NYK) drive.
null
Mobley (CLE) jumps somewhat toward Hartenstein (NYK) at the start of his drive and marginal contact occurs during his drive to the basket.
Allen (CLE) jumps in the air and Randle (NYK) momentarily places his hand to his back but the contact does not affects his ability to defend the pass.
Allen (CLE) brushes Randle's (NYK) shoulder as Mitchell (CLE) cleanly dislodges the ball away from him.
Barrett (NYK) makes contact with the ball after Mitchell's (CLE) gather and dislodges the ball away before incidental arm contact occurs.
Mitchell (CLE) is the last person to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. The possession is correctly given to NYK.
Allen (CLE) places his bent forearm to Randle's (NYK) front during his drive to the basket and marginal contact occurs.
Mobley (CLE) makes contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Randle (NYK) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Barrett (NYK) initiates contact with Mitchell's (CLE) arm after his gather and the contact affects his driving shot attempt.
Okoro (CLE) initiates contact to Brunson's (NYK) front that affects his SQBR during the drive.
Garland (CLE) does not step out of bounds as he receives the pass along the sideline.

Barrett (NYK) already has his arm extended and marginal head contact occurs as Garland (CLE) moves into Barrett's arm and Barrett retreats his arm away. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Okoro (CLE) is firming up with his arms slightly extended as he sets the screen and marginal contact occurs as Barrett (NYK) disengages.
Barrett (NYK) initiates contact with Garland's (CLE) arm as Garland gathers the ball, which affects his SQBR during the driving shot attempt
Okoro (CLE) reaches in and lightly brushes Bruson's (NYK) arm defending his drive to the basket.
Allen (CLE) brings his arm toward Randle's (NYK) front and marginal contact occurs during Randle's (NYK) drive.
Mobley (CLE) jumps vertical as Randle (NYK) jumps into his body and Mobley's arm dislodges Randle's shot attempt at the basket before incidental contact occurs.
Randle (NYK) places his extended arm against Allen's (CLE) body and marginal contact occurs as Allen gathers the loose ball.
A 24 second violations is correctly whistled.
Grimes (NYK) briefly places his hands against Mobley's (CLE) body as they move toward the lane before correcting.
Randle (NYK) brings his arm toward Mitchell's (CLE) path and marginal contact occurs during Mitchell's (CLE) drive.
Hartenstein (NYK) initially jumps vertical but brings his arm down and makes contact to Mitchell's (CLE) arm and affects his driving shot attempt.
null
Randle (NYK) makes marginal contact to Mitchell's (CLE) arm as he releases the pass.
